---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
import CTA from '../../components/CTA.astro';
import FAQ from '../../components/FAQ.astro';

const faqs = [
  {
    q: 'What is involved in a commercial refrigeration design consultation?',
    a: 'A refrigeration design consultation begins with understanding your business needs: what products you will store, required temperatures, frequency of access, future capacity needs, and physical space constraints. John Rigo then performs a load calculation to determine the appropriate refrigeration capacity, recommends equipment and configuration, and produces a design plan that accounts for electrical, drainage, and ventilation requirements. Call <a href="tel:+17605941125">(760) 594-1125</a> to schedule.'
  },
  {
    q: 'Can you design a refrigeration system for a new restaurant or commercial kitchen?',
    a: 'Yes. New commercial kitchen refrigeration design is one of our primary services. We work from your floor plans and menu/volume projections to design a refrigeration layout that supports your operation efficiently — from walk-in coolers and freezers to reach-in units and prep area refrigeration. We coordinate with your contractor and equipment suppliers.'
  },
  {
    q: 'How do Arizona summers affect commercial refrigeration system design?',
    a: 'Significantly. High ambient temperatures in Arizona require refrigeration systems with higher capacity than they would need in cooler climates. Condensing units must be sized to reject heat efficiently even when outdoor temperatures exceed 110°F, which is a common summer condition in Buckeye and the West Valley. Undersized systems fail prematurely and never reach target temperatures. John designs systems with Arizona conditions in mind from the start.'
  },
  {
    q: 'What brands and equipment do you recommend for commercial refrigeration?',
    a: 'We work with leading commercial refrigeration brands including Hoshizaki, True, Manitowoc, Hussmann, Tyler, Bohn, and Copeland. Equipment selection depends on your application, budget, and service requirements. We are brand-agnostic and will recommend what is genuinely best for your situation — not what has the highest margin for us.'
  },
  {
    q: 'Can you help with HACCP compliance and food safety refrigeration requirements?',
    a: 'We are familiar with HACCP (Hazard Analysis Critical Control Point) principles as they apply to refrigeration systems and cold chain requirements. While we are refrigeration technicians rather than HACCP auditors, we design systems that meet the temperature and operational requirements that food safety regulations demand. We are happy to coordinate with your food safety consultant.'
  }
];
---

<Layout
  title="Commercial Refrigeration Design in Buckeye, AZ | Altered Air | (760) 594-1125"
  description="Custom commercial refrigeration design for restaurants, cold storage, and food processing in Buckeye, AZ. John Rigo at Altered Air — (760) 594-1125."
  canonical="/services/refrigeration-design"
>
  <section class="page-hero">
    <div class="container">
      <p class="breadcrumb"><a href="/">Home</a> → Services → Refrigeration Design</p>
      <h1>Commercial Refrigeration Design — Buckeye, AZ</h1>
      <p>
        Getting refrigeration right means designing it right. John Rigo at Altered Air provides
        commercial refrigeration system design services for restaurants, grocery and food retail,
        food processing facilities, cold storage warehouses, and specialty applications throughout
        Buckeye and the West Valley.
      </p>
      <a href="tel:+17605941125" class="phone-link">&#128222; Consultation: (760) 594-1125</a>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section>
    <div class="container">
      <div class="content-two-col">
        <div>
          <h2>Why Refrigeration Design Matters</h2>
          <p>
            Commercial refrigeration equipment is a major capital investment. A system that is
            undersized for your application will run constantly, fail early, and never maintain
            adequate temperatures — costing you in repairs, energy, and lost product. A system
            that is oversized wastes capital and may create humidity problems.
          </p>
          <p>
            In Arizona, the design challenge is compounded by ambient heat. A condensing unit
            designed for Chicago specifications will underperform in a Buckeye summer where ambient
            temps routinely exceed 110°F. Proper design accounts for worst-case conditions — not
            average conditions.
          </p>
          <p>
            The practical consequence is significant: a system specified without accounting for
            Arizona ambient conditions will run hot, underperform on the hottest days, and fail
            earlier than it should — generating far higher lifetime costs than any savings from a
            lower-capacity specification. Getting the design right from the start is the most
            cost-effective refrigeration decision a West Valley food business can make.
          </p>
          <p>
            John Rigo designs commercial refrigeration systems with real-world Arizona conditions,
            your specific operational needs, and long-term reliability in mind. We would rather
            take the time to get it right on paper than spend years fixing a system that was
            poorly specified from the start.
          </p>

          <h2 style="margin-top:2rem;">What We Design</h2>
          <ul class="feature-list">
            <li>Walk-in cooler systems — custom sized for your capacity and access requirements</li>
            <li>Walk-in freezer systems — including blast freezers for food processing</li>
            <li>Multi-zone cold storage facilities</li>
            <li>Commercial kitchen refrigeration layouts</li>
            <li>Grocery and food retail refrigeration systems</li>
            <li>VRF (Variable Refrigerant Flow) commercial systems</li>
            <li>Wine storage climate control systems</li>
            <li>Food processing cold chain refrigeration</li>
            <li>Ice production systems</li>
            <li>Medical and laboratory refrigeration</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
        <div>
          <div class="highlight-box">
            <h3>Starting a New Commercial Kitchen or Food Business?</h3>
            <p>
              Talk to Altered Air before you finalize your floor plan. Refrigeration placement
              affects electrical, plumbing, and HVAC coordination. Getting us involved early
              saves money and headaches later.
            </p>
            <a href="tel:+17605941125" class="phone">(760) 594-1125</a>
            <a href="/contact" class="btn-primary" style="margin-top:0.5rem;">Schedule Consultation</a>
          </div>
          <div class="card" style="margin-top:1.5rem;">
            <h3>The Design-to-Installation Advantage</h3>
            <p>
              When the same team that designs your system also installs it, you avoid the costly
              gap between what was specified and what was built. Altered Air handles design,
              equipment procurement, installation, and commissioning — ensuring your system
              performs exactly as intended.
            </p>
            <a href="/services/refrigeration-installation" class="card-link">Refrigeration Installation →</a>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="bg-gray">
    <div class="container">
      <h2>Our Design Process</h2>
      <div style="max-width:760px;">
        <div class="install-step">
          <div class="step-num">1</div>
          <div>
            <h3>Discovery &amp; Requirements</h3>
            <p>We start with your business: what you store, at what temperatures, in what volumes, with what access frequency. We tour your space or review your construction plans.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="install-step">
          <div class="step-num">2</div>
          <div>
            <h3>Load Calculation</h3>
            <p>We calculate the heat load for your space accounting for Arizona ambient temperatures, insulation values, product load, door openings, and equipment heat rejection.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="install-step">
          <div class="step-num">3</div>
          <div>
            <h3>System Design &amp; Equipment Specification</h3>
            <p>We specify equipment — compressors, condensing units, evaporators, controls — and create a layout that works with your space and trade coordination requirements.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="install-step">
          <div class="step-num">4</div>
          <div>
            <h3>Quote &amp; Approval</h3>
            <p>You receive a complete written quote with equipment specifications, installation scope, and timeline. We walk you through the design in plain language before any commitment.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="install-step">
          <div class="step-num">5</div>
          <div>
            <h3>Installation &amp; Commissioning</h3>
            <p>Our team installs the system, commissions it to manufacturer specifications, and verifies it is performing to design conditions before handover.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section>
    <div class="container">
      <p style="max-width:680px; color:var(--gray-600);">
        Also see: <a href="/services/refrigeration-installation">refrigeration installation</a>,
        <a href="/services/refrigeration-repair">refrigeration repair</a>, and
        <a href="/services/refrigeration-maintenance">refrigeration maintenance</a>.
        We serve businesses throughout <a href="/locations/buckeye-az">Buckeye</a>,
        <a href="/locations/tolleson-az">Tolleson</a>, <a href="/locations/goodyear-az">Goodyear</a>,
        and the entire West Valley.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <CTA
    heading="Plan Your Commercial Refrigeration System Right"
    subtext="John Rigo at Altered Air provides expert commercial refrigeration design for new builds, kitchen renovations, and food processing facilities across the West Valley."
  />

  <FAQ faqs={faqs} heading="Refrigeration Design FAQs" />
</Layout>

<style>
  .install-step {
    display: flex;
    gap: 1.25rem;
    align-items: flex-start;
    padding: 1.25rem 0;
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--gray-200);
  }
  .install-step:last-child { border-bottom: none; }
  .step-num {
    flex-shrink: 0;
    width: 2.5rem;
    height: 2.5rem;
    background: var(--orange);
    color: var(--white);
    border-radius: 50%;
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: center;
    font-weight: 700;
    font-size: 1rem;
  }
  .install-step h3 { margin-bottom: 0.3rem; font-size: 1rem; }
  .install-step p { color: var(--gray-600); font-size: 0.93rem; margin: 0; }
</style>
